TITLE: Targeting current Node.js version in babel.config.json
DESCRIPTION: This configuration demonstrates how to use `babel-preset-env` to transpile code to the current Node.js version. By setting the `node` target to `current`, Babel will only transpile code that is not supported by the currently running Node.js environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/env.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "presets": [
    [
      "env",
      {
        "targets": {
          "node": "current"
        }
      }
    ]
  ]
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Preset Options in babel.config.json
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet demonstrates different ways to specify presets in a Babel configuration, including passing options. It shows that a preset can be specified as a bare string, wrapped in an array, or with an empty options object. All are equivalent if no options are needed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/presets.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
  "presets": [
    "presetA", // bare string
    ["presetA"], // wrapped in array
    ["presetA", {}] // 2nd argument is an empty options object
  ]
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing core-js with yarn
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to install core-js version 3 using yarn. This is a prerequisite for using the 'useBuiltIns' option with Babel Preset Env to automatically inject polyfills.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/preset-env.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
npm install core-js@3 --save
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Customizing Automatic Runtime Import (JSX to JS)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to customize the import source for the automatic runtime using the `@jsxImportSource` pragma. This allows using a custom JSX library instead of React.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/plugin-transform-react-jsx.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
/** @jsxImportSource custom-jsx-library */

const profile = (
  <div>
    <img src="avatar.png" className="profile" />
    <h3>{[user.firstName, user.lastName].join(" ")}</h3>
  </div>
);
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { jsx as _jsx } from "custom-jsx-library/jsx-runtime";
import { jsxs as _jsxs } from "custom-jsx-library/jsx-runtime";

const profile = _jsxs("div", {
  children: [
    _jsx("img", {
      src: "avatar.png",
      className: "profile",
    }),
    _jsx("h3", {
      children: [user.firstName, user.lastName].join(" "),
    }),
  ],
});
```

