TITLE: Traverse and Update AST Nodes JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use @babel/traverse to traverse an AST generated by @babel/parser and update identifier nodes. It parses JavaScript code, traverses the AST, and modifies the name of the identifier 'n' to 'x'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/traverse.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import * as parser from "@babel/parser";
import traverse from "@babel/traverse";

const code = `function square(n) {
  return n * n;
}`;

const ast = parser.parse(code);

traverse(ast, {
  enter(path) {
    if (path.isIdentifier({ name: "n" })) {
      path.node.name = "x";
    }
  },
});
```

