TITLE: Incorrect Preset Configuration (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates an incorrect way of configuring Babel presets.  It shows a preset configuration object that is missing the corresponding preset name, which can lead to unexpected errors.  It highlights the common mistake of not wrapping a preset with options in an array.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/website/blog/2016-10-24-6.18.0.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// incorrect, and current gives a unexpected error message
{
  "presets": [
    "preset",
    { "presetOptions": 'hi' } // gets parsed as another preset instead of being part of the "preset"
  ]
}
```

