TITLE: JSX/TS Builder Aliases Removal
DESCRIPTION: This migration guide explains the removal of the `t.jSX*` and `t.tS*` builder aliases in Babel 8, recommending using `t.jsx*` and `t.ts*` instead.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/v8-migration-api.md#_snippet_63



----------------------------------------

TITLE: Registering Babel with rootMode upward
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure `@babel/register` with the `rootMode` option set to `upward`. This allows Babel to locate the babel.config.json file in the monorepo's root, ensuring consistent configuration across all packages when using `@babel/register`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/config-files.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
require("@babel/register")({
  rootMode: "upward",
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Webpack Entry with Babel Polyfill
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure webpack to include `@babel/polyfill` in the entry array.  This approach ensures that the polyfill is included in the bundled output. It shows how to incorporate Babel's polyfills when `@babel/preset-env` is not used or when its `useBuiltIns` option is not configured to handle polyfills automatically. The `entry` array specifies the starting points for the webpack build process, and including `@babel/polyfill` here ensures that it is loaded before any other application code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/polyfill.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  entry: ["@babel/polyfill", "./app/js"],
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: AST Representation of Dynamic Import in Babel 8 (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the new representation of a dynamic import statement in the AST in Babel 8. The import() expression is now represented by an ImportExpression node, with the source and options as its properties.  This is the recommended way to represent dynamic imports in Babel 8 and later.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/v8-migration-api.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
{
  type: "ImportExpression",
  source: StringLiteral("foo"),
  options: Identifier("options")
}
```

