TITLE: Configuring forceAllTransforms in Babel
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure the `forceAllTransforms` option within the Babel Preset-Env in a `babel.config.js` file. It conditionally enables all transforms when the `production` environment is active, which is useful for ensuring compatibility with older environments or minifiers like UglifyJS.  The `api.env` function is used to access the current environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/preset-env.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
module.exports = function(api) {
  return {
    presets: [
      [
        "@babel/preset-env",
        {
          targets: {
            chrome: 59,
            edge: 13,
            firefox: 50,
          },
          // for uglifyjs...
          forceAllTransforms: api.env("production"),
        },
      ],
    ],
  };
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using Presets in Compilation
DESCRIPTION: Compiles `script.js` to `script-compiled.js` using the specified presets (@babel/preset-env and @babel/flow).  The `--presets` option allows applying pre-configured sets of transformations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/cli.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
npx babel script.js --out-file script-compiled.js --presets=@babel/preset-env,@babel/flow
```

