TITLE: Checking for Function Nodes in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Checks if a given AST node represents a function or method with a body and parameters. It uses the `t.isFunction(node)` method from Babel's `types` API. It covers nodes like `ArrowFunctionExpression`, `ClassMethod`, `FunctionDeclaration`, `FunctionExpression`, and `ObjectMethod`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/types.md#_snippet_273

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
t.isFunction(node);
```

