TITLE: Configuring Babel for Deno target in JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON configuration snippet demonstrates how to configure `@babel/preset-env` to compile for a specific Deno version. The `targets` option is used to specify the Deno version, ensuring that only features not supported by that version are transpiled. This is useful for maintaining compatibility with older Deno engine versions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/website/blog/2022-10-27-7.20.0.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "targets": { "deno": "1.20" },
    "presets": ["@babel/preset-env"]
}
```

