TITLE: Dynamic Babel Configuration with babel.config.js
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to create a dynamic `babel.config.js` file.  It checks the `process.env["ENV"]` environment variable and conditionally adds a plugin to the `plugins` array if the environment is set to "prod". The API object provides access to caching and other Babel features. The function exports an object containing `presets` and `plugins`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = function (api) {
  api.cache(true);

  const presets = [ ... ];
  const plugins = [ ... ];

  if (process.env["ENV"] === "prod") {
    plugins.push(...);
  }

  return {
    presets,
    plugins
  };
}
```

