TITLE: Parsing with @babel/parser - Private Name Tokenization
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how private names (`#priv`) are tokenized differently in Babel 8 compared to Babel 7. In Babel 7, a private name is tokenized as two separate tokens (`#` and `name`), while in Babel 8, it's tokenized as a single `privateName` token.  Dependencies: `@babel/parser`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/v8-migration-api.md#_snippet_70

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { parse } from "@babel/parser";

const { tokens } = parse("class C { #priv }", { tokens: true });
tokens.filter(t => t.start >= 10 && t.end <= 15) // get tokens for `#priv`
// Babel 7
// [
//  Token (#) { value: "#", start: 10, end: 11 },
//  Token (name) { value: "priv", start: 11, end: 15 }
// ]
// Babel 8
// [
//  Token (privateName) { value: "priv", start: 10, end: 15 }
// ]
```

