TITLE: Wrapping TSEnumDeclaration members with TSEnumBody in Babel 8 (TS)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the wrapping of the `members` property of `TSEnumDeclaration` within a new `TSEnumBody` node in Babel 8. This provides a more structured representation of enum declarations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/v8-migration-api.md#_snippet_46

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Example input
enum ColorType {
  Red,
  Green,
  Blue,
}

// AST in Babel 7
{
  type: "TSEnumDeclaration",
  id: Identifier("ColorType")
  members: [
    EnumMember("Red"),
    EnumMember("Green"),
    EnumMember("Blue")
  ]
}

// AST in Babel 8
{
  type: "TSEnumDeclaration",
  id: Identifier("ColorType")
  body: {
    type: "TSEnumBody",
    members: [
      EnumMember("Red"),
      EnumMember("Green"),
      EnumMember("Blue")
    ]
  }
}
```

