TITLE: TypeScript Namespace Compilation to JavaScript (Babel vs TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the difference in output between the TypeScript compiler and Babel when compiling namespaced TypeScript code. It highlights that Babel's lack of type information leads to incorrect references and errors if values aren't explicitly referred to in the same namespace definition.
