TITLE: Transformed instanceof Operator JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet shows the output of the transformation applied by the `@babel/plugin-transform-instanceof` plugin. It uses a helper function `_instanceof` to provide compatibility with the `Symbol.hasInstance` method when available. The function checks if `right` is not null, if `Symbol` is defined and the `right` object has the `Symbol.hasInstance` property, calling it. If those conditions are not met, it falls back to the native `instanceof` operator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/plugin-transform-instanceof.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function _instanceof(left, right) {
  if (
    right != null &&
    typeof Symbol !== "undefined" &&
    right[Symbol.hasInstance]
  ) {
    return right[Symbol.hasInstance](left);
  } else {
    return left instanceof right;
  }
}

_instanceof(foo, Bar);
```

