TITLE: Babel Compilation Task in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a build task using the 'start' build system. It finds JavaScript files in the 'src/**/*.js' pattern, reads them, transforms them using Babel with a specified configuration, and writes the output to the 'build/' directory. The babelConfig object is used to configure Babel, disabling babelrc and enabling source maps.
