TITLE: JavaScript Class Transformation (Default)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how Babel transforms a JavaScript class by default. The transformation includes a `_classCallCheck` function to ensure that the class constructor is called with `new`. Input code must be valid JavaScript.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/website/blog/2021-02-22-7.13.0.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function _classCallCheck(instance, Constructor) {
  if (!(instance instanceof Constructor)) {
    throw new TypeError("Cannot call a class as a function");
  }
}

let Test = function Test() {
  _classCallCheck(this, Test);

  this.x = 2;
};

// You can test the thrown error in the console:
// Uncaught TypeError: class constructors must be invoked with 'new'
Test();
```

