TITLE: Context Access in Decorators (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet highlights the updated semantics for `context.access` methods within decorators. The target object is now expected as the first parameter to these methods, rather than as the `this` receiver, to ensure correct behavior in decorator execution and access to class properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/website/blog/2023-02-20-7.21.0.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
