TITLE: Using environmentVisitor with traverse.visitors.merge (JS)
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use `environmentVisitor` with `traverse.visitors.merge` within a Babel plugin's `Function` visitor.  It collects `AwaitExpression` nodes within an async function body, skipping `ArrowFunctionExpression` nodes.  The `environmentVisitor` ensures the correct `this` context is maintained during the traversal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/helper-environment-visitor.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = (api) => {
  const { types: t, traverse } = api;
  return {
    name: "collect-await",
    visitor: {
      Function(path) {
        if (path.node.async) {
          const awaitExpressions = [];
          // Get a list of related await expressions within the async function body
          path.traverse(traverse.visitors.merge([
            environmentVisitor,
            {
              AwaitExpression(path) {
                awaitExpressions.push(path);
              },
              ArrowFunctionExpression(path) {
                path.skip();
              },
            }
          ]))
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

