TITLE: Proxying a Normal Object JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a proxy for a normal object. It intercepts property access and returns a custom string.  It uses the `Proxy` constructor with a target object and a handler object.  Proxies are not transpiled or polyfilled due to ES5 limitations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/docs/learn.md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// Proxying a normal object
var target = {};
var handler = {
  get: function (receiver, name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
  }
};

var p = new Proxy(target, handler);
p.world === "Hello, world!";
```

