TITLE: Makefile for Babel Compilation
DESCRIPTION: This Makefile automates the process of compiling JavaScript files using Babel. It defines variables for source and destination files, and rules for creating the `lib` directory and compiling each JavaScript file from `src` to `lib`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babel/website/blob/main/website/data/tools/make/usage.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Makefile
CODE:
```
SRC = $(wildcard src/*.js)
LIB = $(SRC:src/%.js=lib/%.js)

lib: $(LIB)
lib/%.js: src/%.js babel.config.json
	mkdir -p $(@D)
	babel $< -o $@
```

